text: 206th may refer to: *206th (Canadien-Français) Battalion, CEF, a unit in the Canadian Expeditionary Force during the First World War *206th Combat Communications Squadron (206 CBCS), an Air National Guard combat communications unit located at Elmendorf AFB, Alaska *206th Field Artillery Regiment (United States), a United States artillery regiment Headquartered at Russellville, Arkansas. T *206th Infantry Division (Germany), a military unit that served during World War II ==See also== *206 (number) *206, the year 206 (CCVI) of the Julian calendar
